## Preamble

{{ company_name }} ("the Organization") handles sensitive and confidential information on behalf of its clients, partners, and internal operations. The Organization has established strict confidentiality commitments with its clients, requiring that all information and materials supplied by clients be kept in confidence, in any and all forms, and not disclosed to third parties without the client's express written permission.

As an employee of the Organization, and as a condition of your employment, you are bound by these same confidentiality obligations. This Agreement defines your responsibilities regarding access to and protection of confidential information.

## Definitions

### Confidential Material

"Confidential Material" includes, but is not limited to, information relating to:

- Client, customer, and partner information (including contracts, communications, account data, and business relationship details).
- Financial transactions (including payment records, billing information, and account balances).
- Lists of individuals containing Personally Identifiable Information (PII) or other protected data categories.
- Third-party proprietary information (including software, vendor data, specifications, and methodologies).
- Internal organizational information (including business strategies, financial data, personnel records, security configurations, and trade secrets).

### Client Data

All client identities, databases, data sets, software enhancements, programs, updates, electronic media, memoranda, and related materials (collectively "Client Data") are the sole property of the Organization and are to be treated as privileged and confidential. Any unauthorized use, access, or disclosure of Client Data is strictly prohibited.

## Employee Obligations

Confidential Material is valuable and sensitive. It is protected by law and by organizational policy. The intent of these protections is to ensure that Confidential Material is used only as necessary to accomplish the Organization's legitimate business purposes.

As an employee, you are required to conduct yourself in strict conformance with applicable laws and organizational policies governing Confidential Material. Your principal obligations are set forth below. Violation of any of these duties may subject you to disciplinary action, up to and including termination of employment and legal prosecution.

### 1. Authorized Use Only

You will use Confidential Material only as necessary to perform your legitimate job duties. Specifically:

- You will access only the Confidential Material for which you have a legitimate business need to know.
- You will not take possession of, divulge, copy, release, sell, loan, review, alter, or destroy any Confidential Material except as properly authorized within the scope of your employment.
- You will not misuse Confidential Material or handle it in a careless manner.
- You will not use Confidential Material for personal benefit or for the benefit of any party other than the Organization.
- Under no circumstances may Client Data be used or disclosed for personal or non-business purposes.

### 2. Safeguarding Access Credentials

You will safeguard and will not disclose your access credentials (usernames, passwords, access codes, tokens, keys, or any other authorization mechanisms) that allow you to access Confidential Material or organizational systems. Sharing of credentials is prohibited.

### 3. Responsibility for Actions

You accept responsibility for all activities undertaken using your access credentials during your employment. You acknowledge that your access may be monitored and logged.

### 4. Reporting Obligations

You will promptly report to your supervisor or to the security team any activities by any individual or entity that you suspect may compromise the confidentiality, integrity, or availability of Confidential Material. Reports made in good faith will be handled confidentially to the extent permitted by law, including protection of the reporting individual's identity where possible.

### 5. Continuing Obligations

Your obligations under this Agreement continue after the termination of your employment, regardless of the reason for termination. The duty to protect Confidential Material does not expire.

### 6. No Ownership Rights

You understand that you have no right, title, or ownership interest in any Confidential Material referenced in this Agreement. The Organization may, at any time and at its sole discretion, revoke your access credentials, authorization, or access to Confidential Material.

### 7. Accountability for Violations

You will be held accountable for any misuse, unauthorized possession, or wrongful disclosure of Confidential Material, and for any failure to safeguard your access credentials. You understand that failure to comply with this Agreement may result in loss of employment, legal liability, and civil or criminal prosecution.

## Acknowledgment

By signing below, I acknowledge that:

- I have read and understand this Employee Access and Confidentiality Agreement.
- I agree to comply with all obligations set forth in this Agreement.
- I understand that any breach of this Agreement may subject me to disciplinary action, up to and including termination of employment, and may result in legal prosecution.
- I understand that my obligations under this Agreement continue after termination of my employment.

